\end{equation}
\item In $\mathcal{I}$: The experiential description $e(\tau)_\text{uncertainty}$ states that precise knowledge of position precludes knowledge of momentum.
\item In $\mathcal{X}$: The complete description $\phi_e^\mathcal{X}$ shows that uncertainty emerges from dimensional reduction during projection from $\mathcal{X}$ to either $\mathcal{O}$ or $\mathcal{I}$.
