\subsubsection{Observer 2's Light Path as Seen by Observer 1}

When Observer 1 (embankment) observes Observer 2's (train) light clock, they see a triangular path due to the train's motion. In standard SR, we calculate:

\begin{itemize}
\item Distance traveled by light (in Observer 1's frame):
  \begin{equation}
