\item For light to travel this distance: $2\sqrt{L^2 + (v\Delta t/2)^2} = c\Delta t$
\item Solving for $\Delta t$: $\Delta t = \frac{2L}{c\sqrt{1-v^2/c^2}} = \Delta t' \cdot \gamma = 2 \cdot 1.6667 = 3.3334$ seconds
